definition: to match/well-suited
each other/one another/mutually/fret on the neck of a pipa 琵琶[pi2 pa5] (a fret on the soundboard is called a 品[pin3])
surname Xiang
appearance/portrait/picture/government minister/(physics) phase/(literary) to appraise (esp. by scrutinizing physical features)/to read sb's fortune (by physiognomy, palmistry etc)
to join/to fit/to mate/to mix/to match/to deserve/to make up (a prescription)/to allocate
match (couple)/persons well suited for each other
thing that is well suited/pet animal that suits its owner

sentences.english: The curtains do not match with the decoration.
sentences.chinese: 窗帘与室内装璜不相配。

sentences.english: Now, improved bedsheets are being designed to be compatible with that technology.
sentences.chinese: 现在，与这一技术相配套的改进床单正在设计当中。

sentences.english: The doors were painted blue to match the walls.
sentences.chinese: 门漆成了兰色，为的是与墙的颜色相配。

sentences.english: Twi have the highest rate of match, followed by siblings .
sentences.chinese: 双胞胎相配的几率最高，接下来是兄弟姐妹。

sentences.english: Is the quality of education matching the quantity of children passing through the school gates?
sentences.chinese: 教育的质量是否与进入小学校门的儿童人数相配？

sentences.english: Acetonitrile continuous recovery plant is a subsidiary part of acrylonitrile production unit.
sentences.chinese: 乙腈连续回收装置是与丙烯腈生产主装置相配套的。

sentences.english: Everyday for the rest of your life, you would thank God that I was the appropriate age for you. But I’m not.
sentences.chinese: 你今后的每一天都会感谢上帝让我与你年龄相配。

sentences.english: They will match you with people who have personalities that appear similar to what you described.
sentences.chinese: 他们会根据你所描绘的性格来寻找与你相配的人。

sentences.english: Her dress went well with the brilliant lights.
sentences.chinese: 她的打扮与闪耀的灯光正好相配。

sentences.english: This mismatch in coefficient is certain to result in instability of the center of gravity.
sentences.chinese: 膨胀系数不相配必须会引起重心不稳定。

sentences.english: The golden silk dress matches well with the bow on your head.
sentences.chinese: 这件金色丝织连衣裙与你头上的蝴蝶结十分相配。

sentences.english: It's a question of getting the right mix of policies to appeal to the electorate.
sentences.chinese: 问题是要有能投合选民心意的一整套相配得当的政策。

sentences.english: His necktie does not match his coat.
sentences.chinese: 他的领带和他的上衣不相配。

sentences.english: Then there is the path to the gate to go with the main tower.
sentences.chinese: 而跟这主寨楼相配应的是通往寨门的路。

sentences.english: Tant shirt looks good on you?
sentences.chinese: 那件衬衫看起来和你很相配？
